ss=\"wikitable\"\n|+District Attorneys of Massachusetts\n!District (Counties)\n!District Attorney<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://electionstats.state.ma.us/elections/search/year_from:2012/year_to:2018/office_id:530/stage:General|title=PD43+ \u00bb Search Elections|website=PD43+|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n!Party\n!Website\n|-\n|Berkshire District\n|[[Andrea Harrington]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://www.mass.gov/orgs/berkshire-district-attorneys-office Link]\n|-\n|Bristol District\n|Thomas Quinn, III\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[http://bristolda.com/ Link]\n|-\n|Cape and Islands District (Barnstable, Dukes, Nantucket)\n|Michael O'Keefe\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|[https://www.mass.gov/orgs/cape-and-islands-district-attorneys-office Link]\n|-\n|Eastern District (Essex)\n|Jonathan Blodget\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://www.mass.gov/orgs/essex-district-attorneys-office Link]\n|-\n|Hampden District\n|Anthony Gulluni\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://hampdenda.com/ Link]\n|-\n|Middle District (Worcester)\n|Joseph Early\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://worcesterda.com/ Link]\n|-\n|Norfolk\n|[[Michael W. Morrissey|Michael Morrissey]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://www.mass.gov/orgs/norfolk-district-attorneys-office Link]\n|-\n|Northern (Middlesex)\n|[[Marian T. Ryan|Marian Ryan]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://www.middlesexda.com/ Link]\n|-\n|Northwestern (Hampshire, Franklin)\n|David Sullivan\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://www.northwesternda.org/ Link]\n|-\n|Plymouth\n|Timothy Cruz\n|{{Party shading/Republican}} |Republican\n|[https://plymouthda.com/ Link]\n|-\n|Suffolk\n|[[Rachael Rollins]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}} |Democrat\n|[https://www.suffolkdistrictattorney.com/ Link]\n|}\n\n=== Registry of Deeds ===\n{{Main|Registry of Deeds (Massachusetts)}}\nAll counties in Massachusetts have at least one [[Recorder of deeds|registry of deeds,]] which is responsible for recording and holding copies of deeds, titles, and other land records within their district.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.masslandrecords.com/|website=www.masslandrecords.com|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> Each registry is run by an elected register of deeds, who serves for 6 year terms. Most counties have one registry, but some are divided into separate districts with their own registry. There are 21 registries.\n{| class=\"wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n|+Registry of Deeds in Massachusetts\n|-\n!County\n!Registry\n!Register<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://electionstats.state.ma.us/elections/search/year_from:2018/year_to:2018/office_id:384/stage:General|title=PD43+ \u00bb Search Elections|website=PD43+|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n!Party\n!Website\n|-\n|[[Barnstable County, Massachusetts|Barnstable]]\n|Barnstable\n|John F. Mead\n|{{Party shading/Republican}}|[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Berkshire County, Massachusetts|Berkshire]]\n|North Berkshire\n|Maria T. Ziemba\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]]\n|\n|-\n|Middle Berkshire\n|Patsy Harris\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|South Berkshire\n|Michelle L. Laramee-Jenney\n|{{Party shading/Independent}}|[[Independent politician|Unenrolled]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Bristol County, Massachusetts|Bristol]]\n|North Bristol\n|Barry J. Amaral\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|Fall River\n|Bernard J. McDonald, III\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|South Bristol\n|Frederick M. Kalisz, Jr.\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|[[Dukes County, Massachusetts|Dukes]]\n|Dukes\n|Paulo C. Deoliveiria\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Essex County, Massachusetts|Essex]]\n|North Essex\n|M. Paul Iannuccillo\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|South Essex\n|John L. O'Brien, Jr.\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|[[Franklin County, Massachusetts|Franklin]]\n|Franklin\n|Scott A. Cote\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|[[Hampden County, Massachusetts|Hampden]]\n|Hampden\n|[[Cheryl Coakley-Rivera|Cheryl A. Coakley-Rivera]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|[[Hampshire County, Massachusetts|Hampshire]]\n|Hampshire\n|Mary K. Olberding\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Middlesex County, Massachusetts|Middlesex]]\n|North Middlesex\n|Richard P. Howe, Jr.\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|South Middlesex\n|Maria C. Curatone\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|[[Nantucket County|Nantucket]]\n|Nantucket\n|Jennifer H. Ferreira\n|{{Party shading/Independent}}|Unenrolled\n|\n|-\n|[[Norfolk County, Massachusetts|Norfolk]]\n|Norfolk\n|William P. O'Donnell\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|[[Plymouth County, Massachusetts|Plymouth]]\n|Plymouth\n|John R. Buckley, Jr.\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|[[Suffolk County, Massachusetts|Suffolk]]\n|Suffolk\n|[[Stephen J. Murphy]]\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Worcester County, Massachusetts|Worcester]]\n|North Worcester\n|Kathleen Reynolds Daigneault\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|-\n|South Worcester\n|Kathryn A. Toomey\n|{{Party shading/Democratic}}|Democrat\n|\n|}<br />\n==Municipal Government==\n{{Main|Administrative divisions of Massachusetts}}\n[[File:Boston city hall.jpg|thumb|alt=Modern concrete building|[[Boston City Hall]]]]\nMassachusetts shares with the five other [[New England]] states the [[New England town]] form of government.  All land in Massachusetts is divided among cities and towns and there are no [[unincorporated area]]s, population centers, or townships. Massachusetts has four kinds of public-school districts: local schools, regional schools, vocational-technical schools, and charter schools. \n\n==Transparency==\nThe state has an [[Freedom of information in the United States#State legislation|open-meeting law]] enforced by the attorney general, and a public-records law enforced by the Secretary of the Commonwealth.<ref name=\"rcfp\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rcfp.org/massachusetts-open-government-guide/foreword|title=FOREWORD|work=rcfp.org}}</ref> A 2008 report by the Better Government Association and National Freedom of Information Coalition ranked Massachusetts 43rd out of the 50 US states in government transparency. It gave the state a grade of \"F,\" based on the time, cost, and comprehensiveness of access to public records.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfoic.org/states-failing-foi-responsiveness|title=States Failing FOI Responsiveness|work=nfoic.org}}</ref> Access to government records and the actions of the Secretary in enforcing the law became an issue in the 2014 campaign for the office. Incumbent William Galvin cited his previous requests that the legislature revise the Public Records Law to facilitate access.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2014/09/13/secretary-state-galvin-faces-criticism-for-keeping-government-secrets/e70pa1N2jfwTzKQyrLMWSL/story.html|title=Secretary of State Galvin faces criticism for keeping government secrets - Metro - The Boston Globe|work=BostonGlobe.com}}</ref> According to the governor, he is exempt from the Public Records Law.<ref name=\"rcfp\" /> A reform law was signed on June 3, 2016 and took effect on January 1, 2017, imposing stricter time limits and lower costs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wbur.org/news/2016/06/03/baker-public-records|title=Gov. Baker Signs Law Overhauling State's Public Records System|website=www.wbur.org}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|United States}}\n*[[Outline of Massachusetts]]\n*[[Index of Massachusetts-related articles]]\n*[[Politics of Massachusetts]]\n*[[Law of Massachusetts]]\n*[[Law enforcement in Massachusetts]]\n*[[Judiciary of Massachusetts]]\n*[[Courts of Massachusetts]]\n*[[United States Congress]]\n*[[United States congressional delegations from Massachusetts]]\n*[[List of United States senators from Massachusetts]]\n*[[Massachusetts's congressional districts]]\n*[[List of United States Representatives from Massachusetts]]\n*[[State governments of the United States]] (comparison)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* [http://www.mass.gov/bb/gaa/fy2010/app_10/ga_10/hcdefault.htm Organizational structure of the Government]\n* {{cite web |url = http://www.stateintegrity.org/massachusetts |title = Massachusetts |author1 = Center for Public Integrity |author2=Global Integrity |author3=Public Radio International |work=State Integrity Investigation: Keeping Government Honest |year=2011 |location=USA }}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.mass.gov/ }}\n*[https://www.law.cornell.edu/states/massachusetts.html Massachusetts legal materials] - [[Legal Information Institute]]\n\n{{Massachusetts}}\n{{Massachusetts government}}\n{{Governments of the United States}}\n\n[[Category:Government of Massachusetts| ]]\n[[Category:State governments of the United States|Massachusetts]]\n", "name_user": "Bluealbion", "label": "safe", "comment": "infobox change", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Massachusetts"}
{"title_page": "Vedat \u015ear", "text_new": "{{Infobox medical person\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name = Vedat \u015ear\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = 1955\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| death_cause = \n| nationality = Turkish\n| education = \n| occupation = \n| years_active = \n| known_for = \n| relations = \n| website =http://www.vedatsar.com/en \n| profession =Professor, Researcher, Psychotherapist \n| field = [[Psychiatry]]\n| work_institutions = [[Ko\u00e7 University]]\n\n[[Istanbul University]]\n[[Hacettepe University]]\n| specialism = [[Psychological trauma]]\n| research_field = \n| notable_works = \n| prizes = \n}}\n\n'''Vedat \u015ear, M.D.''' (born 1955) is a Turkish [[psychiatrist]] and professor who specialises in [[psychological trauma]] and [[dissociative disorder]]. His work is particularly concerned with childhood trauma, the [[epidemiology]] of dissociative disorders,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://expertscape.com/ex/dissociative+disorders|title=Dissociative Disorders: Worldwide - Expertscape.com|website=expertscape.com|access-date=2017-01-04}}</ref> complex [[posttraumatic stress disorder]], [[borderline personality disorder]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Vedat_Sar|title=Researchgate|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com.tr/citations?user=3eoqHGMAAAAJ&hl=en|title=Vedat \u015ear - Google Scholar Citations|website=scholar.google.com.tr|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref> and treatment with [[EMDR]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.emdr-tr.org/Assets/Documents/Content/emdr-e-bulten-nisan.pdf|title=EMDR TR|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n\u015ear was president of the [[International Society for the Study of Trauma and Dissociation]] from 2007 to 2008, and president of the ''European Society for Traumatic Stress Studies'' from 2013 to 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.estss.org/prof-vedat-sar-is-new-estss-president-elct-2013-2015/|title=Prof. Vedat Sar is new ESTSS president elect 2013-2015|website=www.estss.org|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>  Currently, he is a [[professor]] and chair of department of [[psychiatry]] at the [[Ko\u00e7 University]]'s School of Medicine.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://kuh.ku.edu.tr/en/doctor/sar-vedat_1273/info | title=M.D. Vedat \u015ear}}</ref>  Previously, he served as a professor of psychiatry at Istanbul University for more than two decades.\n\nIn early 1990s he founded the ''Clinical Psychotherapy Unit and Dissociative Disorders Program'' in Istanbul University, a clinical research center specialized in dissociation and complex trauma.  The Program contributed to the psychotraumatology studies from a cross-cultural perspective and altered the pre-dominant conception of dissociative identity disorder as a phenomenon isolated to Western world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://psychotraumanet.org/nl/een-moderne-sjamaan-hoe-vedat-sar-de-estss-transformeert-tot-een-slagvaardige-communicatieve|title=Een moderne sjamaan: Hoe Vedat Sar de ESTSS transformeert tot een slagvaardige, communicatieve organisatie {{!}} Psychotraumanet|website=psychotraumanet.org|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>  He has served as an international advisor to the American Psychiatric Association's [[DSM-5]] Workgroup on Anxiety, Obsessive-Compulsive, Post-Traumatic, and Dissociative Disorders.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Spiegel|first=David|last2=Loewenstein|first2=Richard J.|last3=Lewis-Fern\u00e1ndez|first3=Roberto|last4=Sar|first4=Vedat|last5=Simeon|first5=Daphne|last6=Vermetten|first6=Eric|last7=Carde\u00f1a|first7=Etzel|last8=Dell|first8=Paul F.|date=2011-12-01|title=Dissociative disorders in DSM-5|journal=Depression and Anxiety|language=en|volume=28|issue=12|pages=E17\u2013E45|doi=10.1002/da.20923|pmid=22134959|issn=1520-6394}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-JivBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT1531&lpg=PT1531&dq=dsm-5+vedat+sar#v=onepage&q=vedat&f=false|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-5\u00ae)|last=Association|first=American Psychiatric|date=2013-05-22|publisher=American Psychiatric Pub|isbn=9780890425572|language=en}}</ref>  In recognition for his work in the study of dissociation he received various awards including the [[International Society for the Study of Trauma and Dissociation#Honors Bestowed by ISSTD|Lifetime Achievement Award]] by International Society for the Study of Trauma and Dissociation in 2015.\n\nHe and co-author Erdin\u00e7 \u00d6zt\u00fcrk coined the term ''sociological self'', in the context of the \"functional dissociation of the self\" model.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=MD|first=Dr Vedat \u015ear|last2=PhD|first2=Erdin\u00e7 \u00d6zt\u00fcrk|date=2007-11-27|title=Functional Dissociation of the Self: A Sociocognitive Approach to Trauma and Dissociation|journal=Journal of Trauma & Dissociation|volume=8|issue=4|pages=69\u201389|doi=10.1300/J229v08n04_05|issn=1529-9732|pmid=18077285}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sociologyindex.com/dissociation.htm|title=DISSOCIATION. The term dissociation can be used in a psychological way or in a sociological way.|website=sociologyindex.com|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 he was involved with the diagnosis and treatment of a highly publicized \"[[vampire]]\" case in Turkey, which became the subject of an article that was published in the journal of ''Psychotherapy and Psychosomatics''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/Default.aspx?pageID=238&nid=40797|title=Actual 'vampire' found in Turkey|last=|first=|date=|website=H\u00fcrriyet Daily News {{!}} LEADING NEWS SOURCE FOR TURKEY AND THE REGION|publisher=|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://onedio.com/haber/dunyanin-ilk-vampiri-turkiye-de-75424|title=T\u00fcrk Vampirin S\u0131rr\u0131 Ortaya \u00c7\u0131kt\u0131|last=Onedio.com|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=Onedio}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.optimushaber.com/turk-vampiri-tedavi-eden-dr.-vedat-sar-artik-kan-icmiyor-176798h.htm|title=T\u00fcrk Vampiri Tedavi Eden Dr. Vedat \u015ear: \"art\u0131k Kan \u0130\u00e7miyor\"|website=www.optimushaber.com|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/kan-icmeden-duramiyor-gundem-1667278/|title=Kan i\u00e7meden duram\u0131yor|last=sitesi|first=milliyet.com.tr T\u00fcrkiye'nin lider haber|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=M\u0130LL\u0130YET HABER - T\u00dcRK\u0130YE'N\u0130N HABER S\u0130TES\u0130}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/turk-vampir-sagligina-kavustu-gundem-1667184/|title=T\u00fcrk vampir sa\u011fl\u0131\u011f\u0131na kavu\u015ftu|last=sitesi|first=milliyet.com.tr T\u00fcrkiye'nin lider haber|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=M\u0130LL\u0130YET HABER - T\u00dcRK\u0130YE'N\u0130N HABER S\u0130TES\u0130}}</ref>  He frequently provides commentary to the media and participates as a speaker in cross-disciplinary panels about the psychological and sociological dynamics of trauma.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://t24.com.tr/haber/savas-ve-baris-ortaminda-ruh-sagligi-tartisilacak,279110|title='Sava\u015f ve bar\u0131\u015f ortam\u0131nda ruh sa\u011fl\u0131\u011f\u0131' tart\u0131\u015f\u0131lacak|access-date=2017-01-05|language=tr-TR|newspaper=t24.com.tr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.on5yirmi5.com/haber/saglik/hastaliklar/132384/turkiyede-cok-gorulen-5-fobi.html|title=T\u00fcrkiye'de \u00c7ok G\u00f6r\u00fclen 5 Fobi|date=2013-07-23|access-date=2017-01-05|language=tr-TR|newspaper=on5yirmi5.com Gen\u00e7Haber}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/taciz-ve-istismar-haberleri-hassasiyetle-verilmeli-40082071|title=Taciz ve istismar haberleri hassasiyetle verilmeli|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arsiv.sabah.com.tr/2008/03/08/gny/haber,A84AF96E5FBA4C5793D7A3BF1008DC49.html|title=G\u00fcnayd\u0131n - 8 Mart 2008, Cumartesi - En b\u00fcy\u00fck korkumuz performans!|website=arsiv.sabah.com.tr|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.internethaber.com/tedavi-edilmezse-sorun-buyuyor-236974h.htm|title=Tedavi edilmezse sorun b\u00fcy\u00fcyor|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=\u0130nternethaber.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.aktuelpsikoloji.com/dsm-5-taslak-tani-olcutlerine-genel-bir-bakis-11483h.htm|title=DSM-5 Taslak Tan\u0131 \u00d6l\u00e7\u00fctlerine Genel bir Bak\u0131\u015f|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=Akt\u00fcel Psikoloji}}</ref>\n\nAs of January 2017, he was one of the 150 most influential Turkish scientists in terms of [[impact factor]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.memurlar.net/haber/510663/|title=T\u00fcrkiye'nin en ba\u015far\u0131l\u0131 bilim insanlar\u0131 - Memurlar.Net|website=www.memurlar.net|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:\u015ear, Vedat}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Turkish psychiatrists]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox medical person\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name = Vedat \u015ear\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = 1955\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| death_cause = \n| nationality = Turkish\n| education = \n| occupation = \n| years_active = \n| known_for = \n| relations = \n| website =http://www.vedatsar.com/en \n| profession =Professor, Researcher, Psychotherapist \n| field = [[Psychiatry]]\n| work_institutions = [[Ko\u00e7 University]]\n\n[[Istanbul University]]\n[[Hacettepe University]]\n| specialism = [[Psychological trauma]]\n| research_field = \n| notable_works = \n| prizes = \n}}\n\n'''Vedat \u015ear, M.D.''' (born 1955) is a Turkish [[psychiatrist]] and professor who specialises in [[psychological trauma]] and [[dissociative disorder]]. His work is particularly concerned with childhood trauma, the [[epidemiology]] of dissociative disorders,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://expertscape.com/ex/dissociative+disorders|title=Dissociative Disorders: Worldwide - Expertscape.com|website=expertscape.com|access-date=2017-01-04}}</ref> complex [[posttraumatic stress disorder]], [[borderline personality disorder]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Vedat_Sar|title=Researchgate|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com.tr/citations?user=3eoqHGMAAAAJ&hl=en|title=Vedat \u015ear - Google Scholar Citations|website=scholar.google.com.tr|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref> and treatment with [[EMDR]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.emdr-tr.org/Assets/Documents/Content/emdr-e-bulten-nisan.pdf|title=EMDR TR|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n\u015ear was president of the [[International Society for the Study of Trauma and Dissociation]] from 2008 to 2009, and president of the ''European Society for Traumatic Stress Studies'' from 2013 to 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.estss.org/prof-vedat-sar-is-new-estss-president-elct-2013-2015/|title=Prof. Vedat Sar is new ESTSS president elect 2013-2015|website=www.estss.org|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>  Currently, he is teaching as a [[visiting professor]] of [[psychiatry]] at the [[Ko\u00e7 University]]'s School of Medicine.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://kuh.ku.edu.tr/en/doctor/sar-vedat_1273/info | title=M.D. Vedat \u015ear}}</ref>  Previously, he served as a professor of psychiatry at Istanbul University for more than two decades.\n\nIn early 1990s he founded the ''Clinical Psychotherapy Unit and Dissociative Disorders Program'' in Istanbul University, a clinical research center specialized in dissociation and complex trauma.  The Program contributed to the psychotraumatology studies from a cross-cultural perspective and altered the pre-dominant conception of dissociative identity disorder as a phenomenon isolated to Western world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://psychotraumanet.org/nl/een-moderne-sjamaan-hoe-vedat-sar-de-estss-transformeert-tot-een-slagvaardige-communicatieve|title=Een moderne sjamaan: Hoe Vedat Sar de ESTSS transformeert tot een slagvaardige, communicatieve organisatie {{!}} Psychotraumanet|website=psychotraumanet.org|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>  He has served as an international advisor to the American Psychiatric Association's [[DSM-5]] Workgroup on Anxiety, Obsessive-Compulsive, Post-Traumatic, and Dissociative Disorders.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Spiegel|first=David|last2=Loewenstein|first2=Richard J.|last3=Lewis-Fern\u00e1ndez|first3=Roberto|last4=Sar|first4=Vedat|last5=Simeon|first5=Daphne|last6=Vermetten|first6=Eric|last7=Carde\u00f1a|first7=Etzel|last8=Dell|first8=Paul F.|date=2011-12-01|title=Dissociative disorders in DSM-5|journal=Depression and Anxiety|language=en|volume=28|issue=12|pages=E17\u2013E45|doi=10.1002/da.20923|pmid=22134959|issn=1520-6394}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=-JivBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT1531&lpg=PT1531&dq=dsm-5+vedat+sar#v=onepage&q=vedat&f=false|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-5\u00ae)|last=Association|first=American Psychiatric|date=2013-05-22|publisher=American Psychiatric Pub|isbn=9780890425572|language=en}}</ref>  In recognition for his work in the study of dissociation he received various awards including the [[International Society for the Study of Trauma and Dissociation#Honors Bestowed by ISSTD|Lifetime Achievement Award]] by International Society for the Study of Trauma and Dissociation in 2015.\n\nHe and co-author Erdin\u00e7 \u00d6zt\u00fcrk coined the term ''sociological self'', in the context of the \"functional dissociation of the self\" model.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=MD|first=Dr Vedat \u015ear|last2=PhD|first2=Erdin\u00e7 \u00d6zt\u00fcrk|date=2007-11-27|title=Functional Dissociation of the Self: A Sociocognitive Approach to Trauma and Dissociation|journal=Journal of Trauma & Dissociation|volume=8|issue=4|pages=69\u201389|doi=10.1300/J229v08n04_05|issn=1529-9732|pmid=18077285}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sociologyindex.com/dissociation.htm|title=DISSOCIATION. The term dissociation can be used in a psychological way or in a sociological way.|website=sociologyindex.com|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013 he was involved with the diagnosis and treatment of a highly publicized \"[[vampire]]\" case in Turkey, which became the subject of an article that was published in the ''Journal of Psychotherapy and Psychosomatics''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/Default.aspx?pageID=238&nid=40797|title=Actual 'vampire' found in Turkey|last=|first=|date=|website=H\u00fcrriyet Daily News {{!}} LEADING NEWS SOURCE FOR TURKEY AND THE REGION|publisher=|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://onedio.com/haber/dunyanin-ilk-vampiri-turkiye-de-75424|title=T\u00fcrk Vampirin S\u0131rr\u0131 Ortaya \u00c7\u0131kt\u0131|last=Onedio.com|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=Onedio}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.optimushaber.com/turk-vampiri-tedavi-eden-dr.-vedat-sar-artik-kan-icmiyor-176798h.htm|title=T\u00fcrk Vampiri Tedavi Eden Dr. Vedat \u015ear: \"art\u0131k Kan \u0130\u00e7miyor\"|website=www.optimushaber.com|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/kan-icmeden-duramiyor-gundem-1667278/|title=Kan i\u00e7meden duram\u0131yor|last=sitesi|first=milliyet.com.tr T\u00fcrkiye'nin lider haber|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=M\u0130LL\u0130YET HABER - T\u00dcRK\u0130YE'N\u0130N HABER S\u0130TES\u0130}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.milliyet.com.tr/turk-vampir-sagligina-kavustu-gundem-1667184/|title=T\u00fcrk vampir sa\u011fl\u0131\u011f\u0131na kavu\u015ftu|last=sitesi|first=milliyet.com.tr T\u00fcrkiye'nin lider haber|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=M\u0130LL\u0130YET HABER - T\u00dcRK\u0130YE'N\u0130N HABER S\u0130TES\u0130}}</ref>  He frequently provides commentary to the media and participates as a speaker in cross-disciplinary panels about the psychological and sociological dynamics of trauma.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://t24.com.tr/haber/savas-ve-baris-ortaminda-ruh-sagligi-tartisilacak,279110|title='Sava\u015f ve bar\u0131\u015f ortam\u0131nda ruh sa\u011fl\u0131\u011f\u0131' tart\u0131\u015f\u0131lacak|access-date=2017-01-05|language=tr-TR|newspaper=t24.com.tr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.on5yirmi5.com/haber/saglik/hastaliklar/132384/turkiyede-cok-gorulen-5-fobi.html|title=T\u00fcrkiye'de \u00c7ok G\u00f6r\u00fclen 5 Fobi|date=2013-07-23|access-date=2017-01-05|language=tr-TR|newspaper=on5yirmi5.com Gen\u00e7Haber}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/taciz-ve-istismar-haberleri-hassasiyetle-verilmeli-40082071|title=Taciz ve istismar haberleri hassasiyetle verilmeli|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arsiv.sabah.com.tr/2008/03/08/gny/haber,A84AF96E5FBA4C5793D7A3BF1008DC49.html|title=G\u00fcnayd\u0131n - 8 Mart 2008, Cumartesi - En b\u00fcy\u00fck korkumuz performans!|website=arsiv.sabah.com.tr|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.internethaber.com/tedavi-edilmezse-sorun-buyuyor-236974h.htm|title=Tedavi edilmezse sorun b\u00fcy\u00fcyor|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=\u0130nternethaber.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.aktuelpsikoloji.com/dsm-5-taslak-tani-olcutlerine-genel-bir-bakis-11483h.htm|title=DSM-5 Taslak Tan\u0131 \u00d6l\u00e7\u00fctlerine Genel bir Bak\u0131\u015f|access-date=2017-01-05|newspaper=Akt\u00fcel Psikoloji}}</ref>\n\nAs of January 2017, he was one of the 150 most influential Turkish scientists in terms of [[impact factor]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.memurlar.net/haber/510663/|title=T\u00fcrkiye'nin en ba\u015far\u0131l\u0131 bilim insanlar\u0131 - Memurlar.Net|website=www.memurlar.net|access-date=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:\u015ear, Vedat}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Turkish psychiatrists]]\n[[Category:1955 births]]\n", "name_user": "Belowthewings", "label": "safe", "comment": "journalk name changed, position in Ko\u00e7 University corrected.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vedat_%C5%9Ear"}
{"title_page": "K. S. Gopalakrishnan", "text_new": "{{For|the venu player|K. S. Gopalakrishnan (musician)}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = K.S. Gopala Krishnan\n| image         = Mr. KS. Gopala Krishnan.JPG\n| imagesize     =\n| caption       =\n| birth_name    =\n| birth_date    = 1929\n| birth_place   = [[Sakkottai, Thanjavur district|Sakkottai]], [[Tanjore District (Madras Presidency)|Tanjore District]], [[Madras Presidency]]\n| death_date    = {{death date and age|2015|11|14|1929|df=y}}\n| death_place   = [[Chennai]], [[Tamil Nadu]], India\n| othername     =\n| yearsactive   = 1954-92\n| spouse        = sulochana\n| children      = [[K. S. G. Venkatesh]], K.S.G. Ravi and 4 other sons\n| occupation    = [[Film Writer]], [[Film director|Director]], Producer, Lyricist , Studio Owner, Devotional Orator on [[Thiruppugazh]]\n}}\n\n'''K. S. Gopalakrishnan''' was an Indian screenwriter, director, producer, and lyricist, who worked in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Malayalam language|Malayalam]] and [[Hindi]] films.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/07/06/stories/2006070616070200.htm|title=Actor K.R. Vijaya's smile illuminated her acting career|last=Kumar|first=S.R. Ashok|date=6 July 2006|work=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> Since the early 1960s, he directed 70 films. He spent most of his career directing and producing movies with social and devotional themes. Most of his movies are [[melodrama]]s. His son [[K. S. G. Venkatesh]] is an actor who has acted in television serials and in films like ''[[Sathuranga Vettai]]''.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Would-Like-to-Play-Dad-to-Young-Kollywood-Actors/2014/08/05/article2364557.ece</ref>\n\n== Birth and early life ==\n\nIyakkunar Thilagam K.S.Gopalakrishnan was born at Sakkotai near [[Kumbakonam]], Tanjore District in the year 1929 as the eighth son of Shri K. Srinivasan Naidu. When he was about five years old an epidemic orphaned him and his brothers and sisters, when he lost most of the family including his parents. K.S. Gopalakrishnan and his younger brother K.S. Sabarinathan were recommended as juvenile artists to the Shri Nawab Rajamanickam Pillai who was then running a successful professional drama company.\n\nAt that time the Nawab was teaching not only acting to the children of his troupe but also taught them languages, literature, and music. As the Nawab was an ardent nationalist many of his plays propagated the ideals of Mahatma Gandhi and his freedom movement, as well as the ideals of Pandit Nehru, Dr. Rajendra Prasad, Rajaji. The Nawab's troupe performed a play in the presence of Gandhi, who commended the troupe's contribution to the freedom fight.\n\n== Career ==\nAfter serving the Nawab's troupe for about nineteen years in various capacities, K.S.G. joined Sri Devi Nataka Sabha where{{ clarify | date = January 2016 | reason = Is Sri Devi Nataka Sabha a place or a person? }} he wrote two successful plays entitled \u201cPOST-MAN\u201d ,\u201cTHAMBI\u201d(younger brother) and \u201cEZHUTHALAN\u201d(writer).<ref name = sp>https://archive.org/details/dli.bengal.10689.12015/page/n501</ref>\n\n== Entry into film industry ==\nCircumstances pushed KSG to the city of Madras, where he was  accepted as a lyric composer by the Tamil film industry. He was guided by members Kalaivanar N.S.Krishnan and Udumalai Narayana Kavirayar.\n\nLater, he became an assistant to film director Shri Sridar and has worked for several successful   pictures. His first film for which he also wrote the screenplay and dialogue was ''Deivapiravi'', produced by M/S. Kamal Brothers, which acquired a special certificate of merit from Government of India.\n\nFurther success followed as a series of popular hits like Modern Theatre's ''Kumudham'', AVM's ''Annai'', Bala movies' \u201cPadikkatha Medhai\u201d, Unity Pictures' ''Ellam Unakkaha'', and Vasu Films' ''Kai Rasi''.<ref name = sp/>\n\nA.L. Srinivasan requested KSG to direct a picture for him. The result was ''Sarada'', the first and  most successful directorial venture of KSG, which won the coveted State award of Government of India.\n\nThis inspired KSG to produce and direct more hits and gave him the distinction of a hat-trick performer who grabbed the state awards of Government of India continuously for three years for his ''Sarada'', ''Karpagam'', and ''Kai Kodutha Deivam''. After this, as an established director and producer directed more than thirty five pictures in Tamil, Malayalam and a few in Hindi. Many of his films were bought and remade in Telugu and Hindi.\n\nEvery one of his creations was appreciated for the message they carried and the most progressive and impressive ideas they  propagated.{{citation needed|reason=This is an opinion that would be almost impossible to verify.|date=January 2016}} To mention some in particular, his ''Ennathan Mudivu'' was so well received that magazines like ''Kalki'' carried cover-page  photographs of a film director for the first time. Even today, veteran Kamal Hasan made special mention of this film in a screenwriting work shop held at IIT Madras for its extraordinary theme and screenplay by K.S.Gopalakrishnan and how he got inspired by this theme that induced him to produce, write and direct ''Hey Ram''. His ''Panama Pasama'' was a big hit, and Government of the U.S.S.R. invited KSG and his ''Panama Pasama'' to the international film festival held at Tashkent in the year 1968. The festival committee honoured KSG with three certificates of merit and three, special bronze medals. Thus KSG proved that he deserves{{citation needed|reason=Again, how would you verify this opinion?|date=January 2016}} the title \u201cIYAKKUNAR THILAGAM\u201d (Doyen among directors) conferred on him by the public at a function presided over by the A.L. Srinivasan, who was the then President of the South Indian Film Chamber of Commerce.\n\nMany of his films introduced new talents like [[K. R. Vijaya]], [[Jayachitra]], [[Prameela]], [[Vijaya Nirmala]], and several others and gave rebirth to artists like T.K. Bagavathy, S. Varalakshmy, [[B. Saroja Devi]], and [[Padmini (actress)|Padmini]], while he presented the industry with child artists like [[Sridevi]], Shakkeela, Baby Sudha and others.\n\n=== Mythological films ===\n\nSome of his mythological films include ''Adhi parashakthi'' and ''Sri KanchiKamakshi''. He has also produced puranic epics like ''Dasavatharam'', ''Deviyin Thiruvilaiyadal'' and ''Mahasakthi Mariamman''.\n\n== Namefellow ==\nK. S. Gopalakrishnan shared exactly the same name with an earlier director and actor who worked in Tamil cinema in the 1940s and 1950s. This Gopalakrishnan, who directed films produced by S. S. Vasan, did not achieve much cinematic success, and was often confused with the later Gopalakrishnan.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Guy|first1=Randor|authorlink1=Randor Guy|title=Panakkari 1953|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-cinemaplus/panakkari-1953/article3023707.ece|accessdate=10 March 2018|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=26 December 2008}}</ref>\n\n== Iyyakunar Thilagam title ==\n{{Cleanup rewrite|this section is ungrammatical, poorly formatted, and consists almost entirely of peacock phrasing|section|date=January 2016}}\nVeteran Nadigar Thilagam Shivaji Ganesan had a very excellent wavelength with Iyakkunar Thilagam K. S. Gopalakrishnan, and all his films that he worked on with him from the earlier days when KSG was a writer, and then after he elevated to a successful Director and Producer were mega hits. As mentioned above, ''[[Deivapiravi]]'' (Story and screenplay, Dialogues by KSG), [[Padikkadha Medhai|PADIKKATHA METHAI]] (Dialogues), ELLAM UNAKKAGA(screenplay and dialogues), ''[[Kai Koduttha Dheivam]]'' (written, directed and produced by KSG), SELVAM (written and directed), PESUM DHEIVAM (written, directed and produced), KULAMA GUNAMA (written and directed), and PADIKKATHA PANNAIYAAR (written, directed and produced). Of these, KAI KODUTHA DHEIVAM was a sensational hit and bagged the National award. It was in this film where Nadigar Thilagam acted as Mahakavi Bharathiyaar for the evergreen super hit patriotic song \u201cSindhu Nadhiyin misai nilavinile\u201d, which he regarded as an honour to the great poet. All the other movies he worked on with KSG were all mega hits. These movies with the two Thilagams will be entirely different and true to life in KSG's writings and Shivaji's excellent performances.\n\nNadigayar Thilagam Savithri worked for his film AAYIRAM ROOBAI in which the story revolved solely around her character before and after she spots a 1000 rupee note.\n\n''Ellam Unakkaga'' was another film on which he worked as a writer.\n\n== Death ==\nK. S. Gopalakrishnan died on 14 November 2015 at the age of 86.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/film-director-ks-gopalakrishnan-dead/article7879328.ece | title=Film director K.S. Gopalakrishnan dead | publisher=The Hindu | accessdate=15 November 2015}}</ref> He is survived by his wife Sulochana and six sons.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://silverscreen.in/tamil/features/ks-gopalakrishnan-dies-at-86-directed-over-50-films-in-a-storied-career/ | title=KS GOPALAKRISHNAN DIES AT 86; DIRECTED OVER 50 FILMS IN A STORIED CAREER | publisher=Silverscreen | accessdate=15 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n====== As director ======\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Film\n!Cast\n!Notes\n|-\n|1962\n|[[Sarada (1962 film)|Sarada]] \n|[[S. S. Rajendran]], [[C. R. Vijayakumari]] \n|Debut movie\n|-\n|1962\n|[[Deivathin Deivam]] \n|[[S. S. Rajendran]], [[C. R. Vijayakumari]] \n|\n|-\n|-\n|1963\n|[[Karpagam]] \n|[[ Gemini Ganesan]], [[Savithri]] \n|\n|-\n|1964\n|[[Kai Koduttha Dheivam]]\n|[[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[S. S. Rajendran]], [[Savitri (actress)|Savithri]]\n|\n|-\n|1964\n|[[Aayiram Roobai]]\n|[[Gemini Ganesan]], [[Savitri (actress)|Savitri]], [[M. R. Radha]]\n|\n|-\n|1965\n|[[Ennathan Mudivu|En