{"title_page": "K. Amarnath Ramakrishna", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian archaeologist|}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = November 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = K. Amarnath Ramakrishna\n| image              = \n| imagesize          = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = [[Palani, Tamil Nadu]], India\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| restingplace       = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| othername          = \n| education          = [[Institute of Archaeology]], [[Delhi]]\n| occupation         = [[Archaeologist]]\n| yearsactive        = \n| known_for          = Keezhadi Excavation\n| spouse             = \n| domesticpartner    = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| influences         = \n| influenced         = \n| website            = \n| awards             = \n}}\n'''K. Amarnath Ramakrishna''' is an Indian [[archaeologist]]. He is noted for his research into the [[Keeladi excavation site]]''',''' a [[Sangam period]] settlement in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/keezhadi-excavation-the-story-till-now/article18464920.ece|title=Keezhadi excavation leads to ancient civilisation on the banks of Vaigai|last=Desk|first=The Hindu Net|date=2017-05-16|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-10-21|last2=Sundar|first2=S.|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|last3=Sundar|first3=S.|last4=Jesudasan|first4=Dennis S.|last5=Jesudasan|first5=Dennis S.|last6=Jesudasan|first6=Dennis S.|last7=Jesudasan|first7=Dennis S.|last8=Shrikumar|first8=A.|last9=Shrikumar|first9=A.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/society/keezhadi-archaeological-excavation/article10321693.ece|title=A dead city beneath a living village|last=Shrikumar|first=A.|date=2015-08-19|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-10-21|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/keezhadi-excavations-madras-high-court-orders-transfer-of-asi-officer-amarnath-ramakrishna-back-to-tamil-nadu/articleshow/68428874.cms|title=Keezhadi excavations: Madras high court orders transfer of ASI officer Amarnath Ramakrishna back to Tamil Nadu {{!}} Chennai News - Times of India|last=Mar 15|first=Sureshkumar {{!}} TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-10-21|last3=Ist|first3=18:50}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2019/oct/03/keezhadi-a-river-valley-civilization-says-expert-2042669.html|title=Keezhadi, a river valley civilization, says expert|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref> '''Amarnath''' also worked in [[Kondapur]], [[Nagarjunakonda]] museums.\n\n==About Keezhadi Excavation==\nIn 2015, the [[Archaeological Survey of India]] team carrying out excavations in Keezhadi, near Madurai struck gold \u2013 they found the first concrete proof of the existence of a complex and sophisticated urban settlement in ancient Tamil Nadu. Several artefacts found at the site linked it to the [[Sangam era]], a period from 4th Century BCE to 2th century CE widely regarded as a golden era for Tamil culture.\n\nArchaeologist Amarnath Ramakrishna led the team that excavated close to 102 trenches in a 100-acre plot. But in March, the ASI decided to transfer the officer to [[Guwahati]] from the Bengaluru office where he was posted, against his will. He challenged the transfer order before the Central Administrative Tribunal, but it ruled against him. A team is carrying forward the excavation at the [[Keezhadi excavation site|Keezhadi]] site, which now in its third year.\n\nThe transfer, however, kicked up a storm in the state. Political parties in Tamil Nadu, including the [[Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam]], accused the Centre of deliberately trying to derail the excavation as the discoveries made those on the Hindu Right uncomfortable. The parties said Keezhadi could prove their long-held belief that Tamil Nadu may have had a non-Vedic, independent ancient civilisation, something that could challenge the notion of Vedic roots of all of [[Hinduism]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Keezhadi excavation site]]\n*[[Indian Archaeological Society]]\n*[[Tamil Nadu Archaeology Department]]\n*[[Keezhadi]]\n*[[Orissa Balu|Orissa balu]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ramakrishna, K. Amarnath}}\n[[Category:20th-century Indian archaeologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Archaeologists of South Asia]]\n\n\n{{india-scientist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian archaeologist|}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = November 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = K. Amarnath Ramakrishna\n| image              = \n| imagesize          = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = [[Palani, Tamil Nadu]], India\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| restingplace       = \n| restingplacecoordinates = \n| othername          = \n| education          = [[Institute of Archaeology]],[[Delhi]]\n| occupation         = [[Archaeologist]]\n| yearsactive        = \n| known_for          = Keezhadi Excavation\n| spouse             = \n| domesticpartner    = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| influences         = \n| influenced         = \n| website            = \n| awards             = \n}}\n'''K. Amarnath Ramakrishna''' is an Indian [[archaeologist]]. He is noted for his research into the [[Keeladi excavation site]]''',''' a [[Sangam period]] settlement in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/keezhadi-excavation-the-story-till-now/article18464920.ece|title=Keezhadi excavation leads to ancient civilisation on the banks of Vaigai|last=Desk|first=The Hindu Net|date=2017-05-16|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-10-21|last2=Sundar|first2=S.|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|last3=Sundar|first3=S.|last4=Jesudasan|first4=Dennis S.|last5=Jesudasan|first5=Dennis S.|last6=Jesudasan|first6=Dennis S.|last7=Jesudasan|first7=Dennis S.|last8=Shrikumar|first8=A.|last9=Shrikumar|first9=A.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/society/keezhadi-archaeological-excavation/article10321693.ece|title=A dead city beneath a living village|last=Shrikumar|first=A.|date=2015-08-19|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-10-21|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/keezhadi-excavations-madras-high-court-orders-transfer-of-asi-officer-amarnath-ramakrishna-back-to-tamil-nadu/articleshow/68428874.cms|title=Keezhadi excavations: Madras high court orders transfer of ASI officer Amarnath Ramakrishna back to Tamil Nadu {{!}} Chennai News - Times of India|last=Mar 15|first=Sureshkumar {{!}} TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-10-21|last3=Ist|first3=18:50}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil-nadu/2019/oct/03/keezhadi-a-river-valley-civilization-says-expert-2042669.html|title=Keezhadi, a river valley civilization, says expert|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-10-21}}</ref> '''Amarnath''' also worked in [[Kondapur]], [[Nagarjunakonda]] museums.\n\n==About Keezhadi Excavation==\nIn 2015, the [[Archaeological Survey of India]] team carrying out excavations in Keezhadi, near Madurai struck gold \u2013 they found the first concrete proof of the existence of a complex and sophisticated urban settlement in ancient Tamil Nadu. Several artefacts found at the site linked it to the [[Sangam era]], a period from 4th Century BCE to 2th century CE widely regarded as a golden era for Tamil culture.\n\nArchaeologist Amarnath Ramakrishna led the team that excavated close to 102 trenches in a 100-acre plot. But in March, the ASI decided to transfer the officer to [[Guwahati]] from the Bengaluru office where he was posted, against his will. He challenged the transfer order before the Central Administrative Tribunal, but it ruled against him. A team is carrying forward the excavation at the [[Keezhadi excavation site|Keezhadi]] site, which now in its third year.\n\nThe transfer, however, kicked up a storm in the state. Political parties in Tamil Nadu, including the [[Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam]], accused the Centre of deliberately trying to derail the excavation as the discoveries made those on the Hindu Right uncomfortable. The parties said Keezhadi could prove their long-held belief that Tamil Nadu may have had a non-Vedic, independent ancient civilisation, something that could challenge the notion of Vedic roots of all of [[Hinduism]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Keezhadi excavation site]]\n*[[Indian Archaeological Society]]\n*[[Tamil Nadu Archaeology Department]]\n*[[Keezhadi]]\n*[[Orissa Balu|Orissa balu]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ramakrishna, K. Amarnath}}\n[[Category:20th-century Indian archaeologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Archaeologists of South Asia]]\n\n\n{{india-scientist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "BD2412", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Fixing links to disambiguation pages, improving links, other minor cleanup tasks", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Amarnath_Ramakrishna"}
